   1. MINOR PROCEDURES
   ============================================================================ #}

{# --- Control of Minor Tracheostomy Bleeding (Electrocautery) - CPT 12001 --- #}
{% macro minor_trach_bleeding(fio2=40) %}
Minor bleeding was noted from the tracheostomy incision site. Hemostasis did not occur after holding pressure; electrocautery (cautery loop tip) was applied to the bleeding area with FiO₂ confirmed at {{ fio2 }}%. Bleeding ceased after Bovie application. The patient tolerated the intervention well without immediate complications.
{% endmacro %}


{# --- Chemical Cauterization of Granulation Tissue - CPT 17250 --- #}
{% macro chemical_cauterization() %}
Silver nitrate applicators (75% silver nitrate and 25% potassium nitrate) were moistened and applied directly to granulation tissue surrounding the stoma until the tissue was ablated. No complications were observed.
{% endmacro %}


